==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Puppy
<hw>Pup"py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Puppies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F. <ets>poup⟦eacute⟧e</ets>
doll, puppet. See <er>Puppet</er>, and cf. <er>Pup</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The young of a
canine animal, esp. of the common dog; a whelp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A name of contemptuous reproach for a conceited and
impertinent person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I found my place taken by an ill-bred, awkward <qex>puppy</qex>
with a money bag under each arm.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puppy</ent>⟦br⟧

